270
01:58:13,495 --> 01:58:16,487
En route she meets a
roadside Romeo.

271
01:58:16,899 --> 01:58:19,493
She falls in love with him.

272
01:58:20,502 --> 01:58:23,494
Yes! The story spins!

273
01:58:24,506 --> 01:58:26,497
Where is the story?

274
01:58:37,519 --> 01:58:39,510
Get up! Finally
what I said came true!

275
01:58:39,922 --> 01:58:42,516
The boy ran away in the
car without paying up!

276
01:58:43,525 --> 01:58:45,516
- I didn't know...
- How will you?

277
01:58:46,028 --> 01:58:47,461
- You're always sleeping!
- Funny...

278
01:58:48,464 --> 01:58:51,126
Let's go and see
what's the condition.

279
01:58:51,467 --> 01:58:52,798
Hope he hasn't
taken away the fans.

280
01:59:01,977 --> 01:59:03,467
What...? What's the matter?

281
01:59:03,812 --> 01:59:05,473
Where's the husband you came with?

282
01:59:06,482 --> 01:59:09,474
The one in whose car you came.

283
01:59:10,486 --> 01:59:13,148
''- Must be here...
- Taken the bag, luggage... ''

284
01:59:13,489 --> 01:59:15,218
- There's nothing here.
- What?

285
01:59:15,824 --> 01:59:17,485
Who will pay the rent for the room?

286
01:59:17,826 --> 01:59:21,489
She'll pay! She gets clients
to do business! Why won't she pay?

287
01:59:21,897 --> 01:59:23,888
What nonsense! What are you saying?

288
01:59:24,500 --> 01:59:26,161
Pay the room rent.

289
01:59:27,670 --> 01:59:30,503
- I don't have money.
- Then get out of here!

290
01:59:32,508 --> 01:59:34,499
Get out!

291
01:59:35,511 --> 01:59:37,502
- Out
- But where will I go?

292
01:59:37,913 --> 01:59:39,972
None of our concern.
Go to hell!

293
01:59:40,516 --> 01:59:43,508
Drown yourself in a river
but get out of here!

294
01:59:44,520 --> 01:59:47,455
Get out! Did you have to come to
this hotel for soliciting clients?

295
01:59:50,459 --> 01:59:53,451
Don't touch the telephone!
Nor show your face again!

296
01:59:54,463 --> 01:59:57,455
This hotel is for
decent people. Get out!

297
02:00:31,834 --> 02:00:34,997
What's the news?
What's wrong with your voice?

298
02:00:36,505 --> 02:00:39,099
Where are you my dear?
Why are you crying?

299
02:00:39,508 --> 02:00:41,999
Tell me where you are.
I'll come to take you!

300
02:00:44,513 --> 02:00:46,242
Stay there. I'm coming.

301
02:00:50,452 --> 02:00:53,046
- You've made my life.
- Don't mention it.

302
02:00:53,455 --> 02:00:55,787
Your pen has the power.

303
02:00:56,458 --> 02:00:58,187
What a picture you paint!

304
